29uint32 GetTargetFlagMask(SpellTargetObjectTypes objType)
30{
31 switch (objType)
32 {
33 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
34 return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
35 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
36 return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
37 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ALLY:
38 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY;
39 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ENEMY:
40 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
41 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE:
42 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
43 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
44 return TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
45 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
46 return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
47 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
48 return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
49 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_ITEM:
50 return TARGET_FLAG_ITEM;
51 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
52 return TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
53 default:
54 return TARGET_FLAG_NONE;
55 }
56}

63bool SpellImplicitTargetInfo::IsArea() const
64{
65 return GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_AREA || GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CONE;
66}

93float SpellImplicitTargetInfo::CalcDirectionAngle() const
94{
95 switch (GetDirectionType())
96 {
97 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT:
98 return 0.0f;
99 case TARGET_DIR_BACK:
100 return static_cast<float>(M_PI);
101 case TARGET_DIR_RIGHT:
102 return static_cast<float>(-M_PI/2);
103 case TARGET_DIR_LEFT:
104 return static_cast<float>(M_PI/2);
105 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_RIGHT:
106 return static_cast<float>(-M_PI/4);
107 case TARGET_DIR_BACK_RIGHT:
108 return static_cast<float>(-3*M_PI/4);
109 case TARGET_DIR_BACK_LEFT:
110 return static_cast<float>(3*M_PI/4);
111 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_LEFT:
112 return static_cast<float>(M_PI/4);
113 case TARGET_DIR_RANDOM:
114 return float(rand_norm())*static_cast<float>(2*M_PI);
115 default:
116 return 0.0f;
117 }
118}

125uint32 SpellImplicitTargetInfo::GetExplicitTargetMask(bool& srcSet, bool& dstSet) const
126{
127 uint32 targetMask = 0;
128 if (GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TRAJ)
129 {
130 if (!srcSet)
131 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
132 if (!dstSet)
133 targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
134 }
135 else
136 {
137 switch (GetReferenceType())
138 {
139 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
140 if (srcSet)
141 break;
142 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
143 break;
144 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
145 if (dstSet)
146 break;
147 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
148 break;
149 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
150 switch (GetObjectType())
151 {
152 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
153 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
154 break;
155 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
156 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
157 break;
158 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
159 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
160 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
161 switch (GetCheckType())
162 {
163 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
164 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY;
165 break;
166 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
167 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY;
168 break;
169 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
170 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY;
171 break;
172 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
173 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID;
174 break;
175 case TARGET_CHECK_PASSENGER:
176 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER;
177 break;
178 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
179 // nobreak;
180 default:
181 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
182 break;
183 }
184 break;
185 default:
186 break;
187 }
188 break;
189 default:
190 break;
191 }
192 }
193
194 switch (GetObjectType())
195 {
196 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
197 srcSet = true;
198 break;
199 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
200 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
201 dstSet = true;
202 break;
203 default:
204 break;
205 }
206 return targetMask;
207}

324SpellEffectInfo::SpellEffectInfo(SpellEntry const* spellEntry, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 effIndex)
325{
326 _spellInfo = spellInfo;
327 _effIndex = effIndex;
328 Effect = spellEntry->Effect[effIndex];
329 ApplyAuraName = spellEntry->EffectApplyAuraName[effIndex];
330 Amplitude = spellEntry->EffectAmplitude[effIndex];
331 DieSides = spellEntry->EffectDieSides[effIndex];
332 RealPointsPerLevel = spellEntry->EffectRealPointsPerLevel[effIndex];
333 BasePoints = spellEntry->EffectBasePoints[effIndex];
334 PointsPerComboPoint = spellEntry->EffectPointsPerComboPoint[effIndex];
335 ValueMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectValueMultiplier[effIndex];
336 DamageMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectDamageMultiplier[effIndex];
337 BonusMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectBonusMultiplier[effIndex];
338 MiscValue = spellEntry->EffectMiscValue[effIndex];
339 MiscValueB = spellEntry->EffectMiscValueB[effIndex];
340 Mechanic = Mechanics(spellEntry->EffectMechanic[effIndex]);
341 TargetA = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(spellEntry->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex]);
342 TargetB = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(spellEntry->EffectImplicitTargetB[effIndex]);
343 RadiusEntry = spellEntry->EffectRadiusIndex[effIndex] ? sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->EffectRadiusIndex[effIndex]) : NULL;
344 ChainTarget = spellEntry->EffectChainTarget[effIndex];
345 ItemType = spellEntry->EffectItemType[effIndex];
346 TriggerSpell = spellEntry->EffectTriggerSpell[effIndex];
347 SpellClassMask = spellEntry->EffectSpellClassMask[effIndex];
348 ImplicitTargetConditions = NULL;
349}

382 Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PET ||

406
407int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcValue(Unit const* caster, int32 const* bp, Unit const* /*target*/) const
408{
409 float basePointsPerLevel = RealPointsPerLevel;
410 int32 basePoints = bp ? *bp : BasePoints;
411 int32 randomPoints = int32(DieSides);
412
413 // base amount modification based on spell lvl vs caster lvl
414 if (caster)
415 {
416 int32 level = int32(caster->getLevel());
417 if (level > int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel) && _spellInfo->MaxLevel > 0)
418 level = int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel);
419 else if (level < int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel))
420 level = int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel);
421 level -= int32(_spellInfo->SpellLevel);
422 basePoints += int32(level * basePointsPerLevel);
423 }
424
425 // roll in a range <1;EffectDieSides> as of patch 3.3.3
426 switch (randomPoints)
427 {
428 case 0: break;
429 case 1: basePoints += 1; break; // range 1..1
430 default:
431 // range can have positive (1..rand) and negative (rand..1) values, so order its for irand
432 int32 randvalue = (randomPoints >= 1)
433 ? irand(1, randomPoints)
434 : irand(randomPoints, 1);
435
436 basePoints += randvalue;
437 break;
438 }
439
440 float value = float(basePoints);
441
442 // random damage
443 if (caster)
444 {
445 // bonus amount from combo points
446 if (caster->m_movedPlayer)
447 if (uint8 comboPoints = caster->m_movedPlayer->GetComboPoints())
448 if (float comboDamage = PointsPerComboPoint)
449 value += comboDamage* comboPoints;
450
451 value = caster->ApplyEffectModifiers(_spellInfo, _effIndex, value);
452
453 // amount multiplication based on caster's level
454 if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer() &&
455 _spellInfo->SpellLevel && _spellInfo->SpellLevel != caster->getLevel() &&
456 !basePointsPerLevel && _spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_LEVEL_DAMAGE_CALCULATION))
457 {
458 bool canEffectScale = false;
459 switch (Effect)
460 {
461 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
462 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
463 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN:
464 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH:
465 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
466 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
467 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN:
468 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT:
469 case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
470 case SPELL_EFFECT_FORCE_CAST_WITH_VALUE:
471 case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
472 case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_MISSILE_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
473 canEffectScale = true;
474 break;
475 default:
476 break;
477 }
478
479 switch (ApplyAuraName)
480 {
481 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
482 case SPELL_AURA_DUMMY:
483 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
484 case SPELL_AURA_DAMAGE_SHIELD:
485 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_DAMAGE:
486 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
487 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
488 case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_ABSORB:
489 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
490 canEffectScale = true;
491 break;
492 default:
493 break;
494 }
495
496 if (canEffectScale)
497 {
498 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(_spellInfo->SpellLevel - 1);
499 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(caster->getLevel() - 1);
500 if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
501 value *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
502 }
503 }
504 }
505
506 return int32(value);
507}
508
509int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcBaseValue(int32 value) const
510{
511 if (DieSides == 0)
512 return value;
513 else
514 return value - 1;
515}
516
517float SpellEffectInfo::CalcValueMultiplier(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
518{
519 float multiplier = ValueMultiplier;
520 if (Player* modOwner = (caster ? caster->GetSpellModOwner() : NULL))
521 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_VALUE_MULTIPLIER, multiplier, spell);
522 return multiplier;
523}
524
525float SpellEffectInfo::CalcDamageMultiplier(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
526{
527 float multiplier = DamageMultiplier;
528 if (Player* modOwner = (caster ? caster->GetSpellModOwner() : NULL))
529 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_DAMAGE_MULTIPLIER, multiplier, spell);
530 return multiplier;
531}
532
533bool SpellEffectInfo::HasRadius() const
534{
535 return RadiusEntry != NULL;
536}
537
538float SpellEffectInfo::CalcRadius(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
539{
540 if (!HasRadius())
541 return 0.0f;
542
543 float radius = RadiusEntry->RadiusMin;
544 if (caster)
545 {
546 radius += RadiusEntry->RadiusPerLevel * caster->getLevel();
547 radius = std::min(radius, RadiusEntry->RadiusMax);
548 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
549 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RADIUS, radius, spell);
550 }
551
552 return radius;
553}

555uint32 SpellEffectInfo::GetProvidedTargetMask() const
556{
557 return GetTargetFlagMask(TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(TargetB.GetObjectType());
558}
559
560uint32 SpellEffectInfo::GetMissingTargetMask(bool srcSet /*= false*/, bool dstSet /*= false*/, uint32 mask /*=0*/) const
561{
562 uint32 effImplicitTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(GetUsedTargetObjectType());
563 uint32 providedTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(TargetB.GetObjectType()) | mask;
564
565 // remove all flags covered by effect target mask
566 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
567 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK);
568 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)
569 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK);
570 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM)
571 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_ITEM);
572 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT)
573 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
574 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
575 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
576 if (dstSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
577 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
578 if (srcSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
579 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION);
580
581 return effImplicitTargetMask;
582}

764SpellInfo::SpellInfo(SpellEntry const* spellEntry)
765{
766 Id = spellEntry->Id;
767 CategoryEntry = spellEntry->Category ? sSpellCategoryStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->Category) : NULL;
768 Dispel = spellEntry->Dispel;
769 Mechanic = spellEntry->Mechanic;
770 Attributes = spellEntry->Attributes;
771 AttributesEx = spellEntry->AttributesEx;
772 AttributesEx2 = spellEntry->AttributesEx2;
773 AttributesEx3 = spellEntry->AttributesEx3;
774 AttributesEx4 = spellEntry->AttributesEx4;
775 AttributesEx5 = spellEntry->AttributesEx5;
776 AttributesEx6 = spellEntry->AttributesEx6;
777 AttributesEx7 = spellEntry->AttributesEx7;
778 AttributesCu = 0;
779 Stances = MAKE_PAIR64(spellEntry->Stances[0], spellEntry->Stances[1]);
780 StancesNot = MAKE_PAIR64(spellEntry->StancesNot[0], spellEntry->StancesNot[1]);
781 Targets = spellEntry->Targets;
782 TargetCreatureType = spellEntry->TargetCreatureType;
783 RequiresSpellFocus = spellEntry->RequiresSpellFocus;
784 FacingCasterFlags = spellEntry->FacingCasterFlags;
785 CasterAuraState = spellEntry->CasterAuraState;
786 TargetAuraState = spellEntry->TargetAuraState;
787 CasterAuraStateNot = spellEntry->CasterAuraStateNot;
788 TargetAuraStateNot = spellEntry->TargetAuraStateNot;
789 CasterAuraSpell = spellEntry->casterAuraSpell;
790 TargetAuraSpell = spellEntry->targetAuraSpell;
791 ExcludeCasterAuraSpell = spellEntry->excludeCasterAuraSpell;
792 ExcludeTargetAuraSpell = spellEntry->excludeTargetAuraSpell;
793 CastTimeEntry = spellEntry->CastingTimeIndex ? sSpellCastTimesStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->CastingTimeIndex) : NULL;
794 RecoveryTime = spellEntry->RecoveryTime;
795 CategoryRecoveryTime = spellEntry->CategoryRecoveryTime;
796 StartRecoveryCategory = spellEntry->StartRecoveryCategory;
797 StartRecoveryTime = spellEntry->StartRecoveryTime;
798 InterruptFlags = spellEntry->InterruptFlags;
799 AuraInterruptFlags = spellEntry->AuraInterruptFlags;
800 ChannelInterruptFlags = spellEntry->ChannelInterruptFlags;
801 ProcFlags = spellEntry->procFlags;
802 ProcChance = spellEntry->procChance;
803 ProcCharges = spellEntry->procCharges;
804 MaxLevel = spellEntry->maxLevel;
805 BaseLevel = spellEntry->baseLevel;
806 SpellLevel = spellEntry->spellLevel;
807 DurationEntry = spellEntry->DurationIndex ? sSpellDurationStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->DurationIndex) : NULL;
808 PowerType = spellEntry->powerType;
809 ManaCost = spellEntry->manaCost;
810 ManaCostPerlevel = spellEntry->manaCostPerlevel;
811 ManaPerSecond = spellEntry->manaPerSecond;
812 ManaPerSecondPerLevel = spellEntry->manaPerSecondPerLevel;
813 ManaCostPercentage = spellEntry->ManaCostPercentage;
814 RuneCostID = spellEntry->runeCostID;
815 RangeEntry = spellEntry->rangeIndex ? sSpellRangeStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->rangeIndex) : NULL;
816 Speed = spellEntry->speed;
817 StackAmount = spellEntry->StackAmount;
818 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
819 Totem[i] = spellEntry->Totem[i];
820
821 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; ++i)
822 Reagent[i] = spellEntry->Reagent[i];
823
824 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; ++i)
825 ReagentCount[i] = spellEntry->ReagentCount[i];
826
827 EquippedItemClass = spellEntry->EquippedItemClass;
828 EquippedItemSubClassMask = spellEntry->EquippedItemSubClassMask;
829 EquippedItemInventoryTypeMask = spellEntry->EquippedItemInventoryTypeMask;

831 TotemCategory[i] = spellEntry->TotemCategory[i];

834 SpellVisual[i] = spellEntry->SpellVisual[i];
835

963
964bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityLearnedWithProfession() const
965{
966 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
967
968 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
969 {
970 SkillLineAbilityEntry const* pAbility = _spell_idx->second;
971 if (!pAbility || pAbility->AutolearnType != SKILL_LINE_ABILITY_LEARNED_ON_SKILL_VALUE)
972 continue;
973
974 if (pAbility->req_skill_value > 0)
975 return true;
976 }
977
978 return false;
979}
980
981bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityOfSkillType(uint32 skillType) const
982{
983 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
984
985 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
986 if (_spell_idx->second->skillId == uint32(skillType))
987 return true;
988
989 return false;
990}

1012}
1013
1014bool SpellInfo::NeedsToBeTriggeredByCaster(SpellInfo const* triggeringSpell) const
1015{
1016 if (NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
1017 return true;
1018
1019 /*
1020 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1021 {
1022 if (Effects[i].IsEffect())
1023 {
1024 if (Effects[i].TargetA.GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL
1025 || Effects[i].TargetB.GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL)
1026 return true;
1027 }
1028 }
1029 */
1030
1031 if (triggeringSpell->IsChanneled())
1032 {
1033 uint32 mask = 0;
1034 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1035 {
1036 if (Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER && Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_DEST_CASTER
1037 && Effects[i].TargetB.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER && Effects[i].TargetB.GetTarget() != TARGET_DEST_CASTER)
1038 {
1039 mask |= Effects[i].GetProvidedTargetMask();
1040 }
1041 }
1042
1043 if (mask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1044 return true;
1045 }
1046
1047 return false;
1048}

1055bool SpellInfo::IsAutocastable() const
1056{
1057 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE))
1058 return false;

1060 return false;
1061 return true;
1062}
1063
1064bool SpellInfo::IsStackableWithRanks() const
1065{
1066 if (IsPassive())
1067 return false;
1068 if (PowerType != POWER_MANA && PowerType != POWER_HEALTH)
1069 return false;
1070 if (IsProfessionOrRiding())
1071 return false;
1072
1073 if (IsAbilityLearnedWithProfession())
1074 return false;
1075
1076 // All stance spells. if any better way, change it.
1077 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1078 {
1079 switch (SpellFamilyName)
1080 {
1081 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
1082 // Paladin aura Spell
1083 if (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID)
1084 return false;
1085 break;
1086 case SPELLFAMILY_DRUID:
1087 // Druid form Spell
1088 if (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA &&
1089 Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT)
1090 return false;
1091 break;
1092 }
1093 }
1094 return true;
1095}

1210bool SpellInfo::CanPierceImmuneAura(SpellInfo const* aura) const
1211{
1212 // these spells pierce all avalible spells (Resurrection Sickness for example)
1213 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY))
1214 return true;
1215
1216 // these spells (Cyclone for example) can pierce all... // ...but not these (Divine shield, Ice block, Cyclone and Banish for example)
1217 if ((HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_UNAFFECTED_BY_SCHOOL_IMMUNE)) && !(aura && (aura->Mechanic == MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD || aura->Mechanic == MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY || aura->Mechanic == MECHANIC_BANISH)))
1218 return true;
1219
1220 return false;
1221}
1222
1223bool SpellInfo::CanDispelAura(SpellInfo const* aura) const
1224{
1225 // These spells (like Mass Dispel) can dispell all auras, except death persistent ones (like Dungeon and Battleground Deserter)
1226 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY) && !aura->IsDeathPersistent())
1227 return true;
1228
1229 // These auras (like Divine Shield) can't be dispelled
1230 if (aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY))
1231 return false;
1232
1233 // These auras (Cyclone for example) are not dispelable
1234 if (aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_UNAFFECTED_BY_SCHOOL_IMMUNE))
1235 return false;
1236
1237 return true;
1238}

1308
1309SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckShapeshift(uint32 form) const
1310{
1311 // talents that learn spells can have stance requirements that need ignore
1312 // (this requirement only for client-side stance show in talent description)
1313 if (GetTalentSpellCost(Id) > 0 &&
1314 (Effects[0].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[1].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[2].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL))
1315 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1316
1317 uint64 stanceMask = (form ? UI64LIT(1) << (form - 1) : 0);
1318
1319 if (stanceMask & StancesNot) // can explicitly not be cast in this stance
1320 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1321
1322 if (stanceMask & Stances) // can explicitly be cast in this stance
1323 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1324
1325 bool actAsShifted = false;
1326 SpellShapeshiftEntry const* shapeInfo = NULL;
1327 if (form > 0)
1328 {
1329 shapeInfo = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(form);
1330 if (!shapeInfo)
1331 {
1332 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "GetErrorAtShapeshiftedCast: unknown shapeshift %u", form);
1333 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1334 }
1335 actAsShifted = !(shapeInfo->flags1 & 1); // shapeshift acts as normal form for spells
1336 }
1337
1338 if (actAsShifted)
1339 {
1340 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NOT_SHAPESHIFT)) // not while shapeshifted
1341 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1342 else if (Stances != 0) // needs other shapeshift
1343 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1344 }
1345 else
1346 {
1347 // needs shapeshift
1348 if (!HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_NOT_NEED_SHAPESHIFT) && Stances != 0)
1349 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1350 }
1351
1352 // Check if stance disables cast of not-stance spells
1353 // Example: cannot cast any other spells in zombie or ghoul form
1354 /// @todo Find a way to disable use of these spells clientside
1355 if (shapeInfo && shapeInfo->flags1 & 0x400)
1356 {
1357 if (!(stanceMask & Stances))
1358 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1359 }
1360
1361 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1362}
1363
1364SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckLocation(uint32 map_id, uint32 zone_id, uint32 area_id, Player const* player) const
1365{
1366 // normal case
1367 if (AreaGroupId > 0)
1368 {
1369 bool found = false;
1370 AreaGroupEntry const* groupEntry = sAreaGroupStore.LookupEntry(AreaGroupId);
1371 while (groupEntry)
1372 {
1373 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_GROUP_AREA_IDS; ++i)
1374 if (groupEntry->AreaId[i] == zone_id || groupEntry->AreaId[i] == area_id)
1375 found = true;
1376 if (found || !groupEntry->nextGroup)
1377 break;
1378 // Try search in next group
1379 groupEntry = sAreaGroupStore.LookupEntry(groupEntry->nextGroup);
1380 }
1381
1382 if (!found)
1383 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1384 }
1385
1386 // continent limitation (virtual continent)
1387 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_CAST_ONLY_IN_OUTLAND))
1388 {
1389 uint32 v_map = GetVirtualMapForMapAndZone(map_id, zone_id);
1390 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(v_map);
1391 if (!mapEntry || mapEntry->addon < 1 || !mapEntry->IsContinent())
1392 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1393 }
1394
1395 // raid instance limitation
1396 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCE))
1397 {
1398 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1399 if (!mapEntry || mapEntry->IsRaid())
1400 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCE;
1401 }
1402
1403 // DB base check (if non empty then must fit at least single for allow)
1404 SpellAreaMapBounds saBounds = sSpellMgr->GetSpellAreaMapBounds(Id);
1405 if (saBounds.first != saBounds.second)
1406 {
1407 for (SpellAreaMap::const_iterator itr = saBounds.first; itr != saBounds.second; ++itr)
1408 {
1409 if (itr->second.IsFitToRequirements(player, zone_id, area_id))
1410 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1411 }
1412 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1413 }
1414
1415 // bg spell checks
1416 switch (Id)
1417 {
1418 case 23333: // Warsong Flag
1419 case 23335: // Silverwing Flag
1420 return map_id == 489 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1421 case 34976: // Netherstorm Flag
1422 return map_id == 566 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1423 case 2584: // Waiting to Resurrect
1424 case 22011: // Spirit Heal Channel
1425 case 22012: // Spirit Heal
1426 case 24171: // Resurrection Impact Visual
1427 case 42792: // Recently Dropped Flag
1428 case 43681: // Inactive
1429 case 44535: // Spirit Heal (mana)
1430 {
1431 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1432 if (!mapEntry)
1433 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1434
1435 return zone_id == 4197 || (mapEntry->IsBattleground() && player && player->InBattleground()) ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1436 }
1437 case 44521: // Preparation
1438 {
1439 if (!player)
1440 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1441
1442 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1443 if (!mapEntry)
1444 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1445
1446 if (!mapEntry->IsBattleground())
1447 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1448
1449 Battleground* bg = player->GetBattleground();
1450 return bg && bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_JOIN ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1451 }
1452 case 32724: // Gold Team (Alliance)
1453 case 32725: // Green Team (Alliance)
1454 case 35774: // Gold Team (Horde)
1455 case 35775: // Green Team (Horde)
1456 {
1457 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1458 if (!mapEntry)
1459 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1460
1461 return mapEntry->IsBattleArena() && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1462 }
1463 case 32727: // Arena Preparation
1464 {
1465 if (!player)
1466 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1467
1468 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1469 if (!mapEntry)
1470 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1471
1472 if (!mapEntry->IsBattleArena())
1473 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1474
1475 Battleground* bg = player->GetBattleground();
1476 return bg && bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_JOIN ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1477 }
1478 }
1479
1480 // aura limitations
1481 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1482 {
1483 if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1484 continue;
1485 switch (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
1486 {
1487 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED:
1488 case SPELL_AURA_FLY:
1489 {
1490 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
1491 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator skillIter = bounds.first; skillIter != bounds.second; ++skillIter)
1492 {
1493 if (skillIter->second->skillId == SKILL_MOUNTS)
1494 if (player && !player->CanFlyInZone(map_id, zone_id))
1495 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1496 }
1497 break;
1498 }
1499 }
1500 }
1501 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1502}
1503
1504SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, bool implicit) const
1505{
1506 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_CANT_TARGET_SELF) && caster == target)
1507 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1508
1509 // check visibility - ignore stealth for implicit (area) targets
1510 if (!HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_INVISIBLE) && !caster->CanSeeOrDetect(target, implicit))
1511 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1512
1513 Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
1514
1515 // creature/player specific target checks
1516 if (unitTarget)
1517 {
1518 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_CANT_TARGET_IN_COMBAT))
1519 {
1520 if (unitTarget->IsInCombat())
1521 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
1522 // player with active pet counts as a player in combat
1523 else if (Player const* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1524 if (Pet* pet = player->GetPet())
1525 if (pet->GetVictim() && !pet->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CONTROLLED))
1526 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
1527 }
1528
1529 // only spells with SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS can target ghosts
1530 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS) != unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_GHOST))
1531 {
1532 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS))
1533 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_GHOST;
1534 else
1535 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1536 }
1537
1538 if (caster != unitTarget)
1539 {
1540 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1541 {
1542 // Do not allow these spells to target creatures not tapped by us (Banish, Polymorph, many quest spells)
1543 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CANT_TARGET_TAPPED))
1544 if (Creature const* targetCreature = unitTarget->ToCreature())
1545 if (targetCreature->hasLootRecipient() && !targetCreature->isTappedBy(caster->ToPlayer()))
1546 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_CAST_ON_TAPPED;
1547
1548 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_PICKPOCKET))
1549 {
1550 if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1551 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1552 else if ((unitTarget->GetCreatureTypeMask() & CREATURE_TYPEMASK_HUMANOID_OR_UNDEAD) == 0)
1553 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_POCKETS;
1554 }
1555
1556 // Not allow disarm unarmed player
1557 if (Mechanic == MECHANIC_DISARM)
1558 {
1559 if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1560 {
1561 Player const* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer();
1562 if (!player->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK) || !player->IsUseEquipedWeapon(true))
1563 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1564 }
1565 else if (!unitTarget->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID))
1566 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1567 }
1568 }
1569 }
1570 }
1571 // corpse specific target checks
1572 else if (Corpse const* corpseTarget = target->ToCorpse())
1573 {
1574 // cannot target bare bones
1575 if (corpseTarget->GetType() == CORPSE_BONES)
1576 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1577 // we have to use owner for some checks (aura preventing resurrection for example)
1578 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
1579 unitTarget = owner;
1580 // we're not interested in corpses without owner
1581 else
1582 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1583 }
1584 // other types of objects - always valid
1585 else return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1586
1587 // corpseOwner and unit specific target checks
1588 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_PLAYERS) && !unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1589 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_PLAYER;
1590
1591 if (!IsAllowingDeadTarget() && !unitTarget->IsAlive())
1592 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGETS_DEAD;
1593
1594 // check this flag only for implicit targets (chain and area), allow to explicitly target units for spells like Shield of Righteousness
1595 if (implicit && HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CANT_TARGET_CROWD_CONTROLLED) && !unitTarget->CanFreeMove())
1596 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1597
1598 // checked in Unit::IsValidAttack/AssistTarget, shouldn't be checked for ENTRY targets
1599 //if (!HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_UNTARGETABLE) && target->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE))
1600 // return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1601
1602 //if (!HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_POSSESSED_FRIENDS)
1603
1604 if (!CheckTargetCreatureType(unitTarget))
1605 {
1606 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1607 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_IS_PLAYER;
1608 else
1609 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1610 }
1611
1612 // check GM mode and GM invisibility - only for player casts (npc casts are controlled by AI) and negative spells
1613 if (unitTarget != caster && (caster->IsControlledByPlayer() || !IsPositive()) && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1614 {
1615 if (!unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsVisible())
1616 return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1617
1618 if (unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsGameMaster())
1619 return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1620 }
1621
1622 // not allow casting on flying player
1623 if (unitTarget->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_IN_FLIGHT) && !(AttributesCu & SPELL_ATTR0_CU_ALLOW_INFLIGHT_TARGET))
1624 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1625
1626 /* TARGET_UNIT_MASTER gets blocked here for passengers, because the whole idea of this check is to
1627 not allow passengers to be implicitly hit by spells, however this target type should be an exception,
1628 if this is left it kills spells that award kill credit from vehicle to master (few spells),
1629 the use of these 2 covers passenger target check, logically, if vehicle cast this to master it should always hit
1630 him, because it would be it's passenger, there's no such case where this gets to fail legitimacy, this problem
1631 cannot be solved from within the check in other way since target type cannot be called for the spell currently
1632 Spell examples: [ID - 52864 Devour Water, ID - 52862 Devour Wind, ID - 49370 Wyrmrest Defender: Destabilize Azure Dragonshrine Effect] */
1633 if (!caster->IsVehicle() && !(caster->GetCharmerOrOwner() == target))
1634 {
1635 if (TargetAuraState && !unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraState), this, caster))
1636 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1637
1638 if (TargetAuraStateNot && unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraStateNot), this, caster))
1639 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1640 }
1641
1642 if (TargetAuraSpell && !unitTarget->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(TargetAuraSpell, caster)))
1643 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1644
1645 if (ExcludeTargetAuraSpell && unitTarget->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(ExcludeTargetAuraSpell, caster)))
1646 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1647
1648 if (unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION))
1649 if (HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_SELF_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_NEW))
1650 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_CANNOT_BE_RESURRECTED;
1651
1652 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1653}
1654
1655SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckExplicitTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, Item const* itemTarget) const
1656{
1657 uint32 neededTargets = GetExplicitTargetMask();
1658 if (!target)
1659 {
1660 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK))
1661 if (!(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM) || !itemTarget)
1662 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1663 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1664 }
1665
1666 if (Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit())
1667 {
1668 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER))
1669 {
1670 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY)
1671 if (caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unitTarget, this))
1672 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1673 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY
1674 || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY && caster->IsInPartyWith(unitTarget))
1675 || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID && caster->IsInRaidWith(unitTarget)))
1676 if (caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, this))
1677 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1678 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET)
1679 if (unitTarget->GetGUID() == caster->GetCritterGUID())
1680 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1681 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER)
1682 if (unitTarget->IsOnVehicle(caster))
1683 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1684 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1685 }
1686 }
1687 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1688}
1689
1690SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckVehicle(Unit const* caster) const
1691{
1692 // All creatures should be able to cast as passengers freely, restriction and attribute are only for players
1693 if (caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1694 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1695
1696 Vehicle* vehicle = caster->GetVehicle();
1697 if (vehicle)
1698 {
1699 uint16 checkMask = 0;
1700 for (uint8 effIndex = EFFECT_0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
1701 {
1702 if (Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT)
1703 {
1704 SpellShapeshiftEntry const* shapeShiftEntry = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(Effects[effIndex].MiscValue);
1705 if (shapeShiftEntry && (shapeShiftEntry->flags1 & 1) == 0) // unk flag
1706 checkMask |= VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_UNCONTROLLED;
1707 break;
1708 }
1709 }
1710
1711 if (HasAura(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED))
1712 checkMask |= VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_CAST_MOUNT_SPELL;
1713
1714 if (!checkMask)
1715 checkMask = VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_ATTACK;
1716
1717 VehicleSeatEntry const* vehicleSeat = vehicle->GetSeatForPassenger(caster);
1718 if (!HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CASTABLE_WHILE_ON_VEHICLE) && !HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CASTABLE_WHILE_MOUNTED)
1719 && (vehicleSeat->m_flags & checkMask) != checkMask)
1720 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_DO_THAT_RIGHT_NOW;
1721
1722 // Can only summon uncontrolled minions/guardians when on controlled vehicle
1723 if (vehicleSeat->m_flags & (VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_CONTROL | VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_UNK2))
1724 {
1725 for (uint32 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1726 {
1727 if (Effects[i].Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON)
1728 continue;
1729
1730 SummonPropertiesEntry const* props = sSummonPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(Effects[i].MiscValueB);
1731 if (props && props->Category != SUMMON_CATEGORY_WILD)
1732 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_DO_THAT_RIGHT_NOW;
1733 }
1734 }
1735 }
1736
1737 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1738}

1740bool SpellInfo::CheckTargetCreatureType(Unit const* target) const
1741{
1742 // Curse of Doom & Exorcism: not find another way to fix spell target check :/
1743 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK && GetCategory() == 1179)

1757 return !TargetCreatureType || !creatureType || (creatureType & TargetCreatureType);

1832
1833AuraStateType SpellInfo::GetAuraState() const
1834{
1835 // Seals
1836 if (GetSpellSpecific() == SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL)
1837 return AURA_STATE_JUDGEMENT;
1838
1839 // Conflagrate aura state on Immolate and Shadowflame
1840 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK &&
1841 // Immolate
1842 ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 4) ||
1843 // Shadowflame
1844 (SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 2)))
1845 return AURA_STATE_CONFLAGRATE;
1846
1847 // Faerie Fire (druid versions)
1848 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
1849 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
1850
1851 // Sting (hunter's pet ability)
1852 if (GetCategory() == 1133)
1853 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
1854
1855 // Victorious
1856 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00040000)
1857 return AURA_STATE_WARRIOR_VICTORY_RUSH;
1858
1859 // Swiftmend state on Regrowth & Rejuvenation
1860 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x50)
1861 return AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND;
1862
1863 // Deadly poison aura state
1864 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x10000)
1865 return AURA_STATE_DEADLY_POISON;
1866
1867 // Enrage aura state
1868 if (Dispel == DISPEL_ENRAGE)
1869 return AURA_STATE_ENRAGE;
1870
1871 // Bleeding aura state
1872 if (GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & 1<<MECHANIC_BLEED)
1873 return AURA_STATE_BLEEDING;
1874
1875 if (GetSchoolMask() & SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_FROST)
1876 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1877 if (Effects[i].IsAura() && (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN
1878 || Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT))
1879 return AURA_STATE_FROZEN;
1880
1881 switch (Id)
1882 {
1883 case 71465: // Divine Surge
1884 case 50241: // Evasive Charges
1885 return AURA_STATE_UNKNOWN22;
1886 default:
1887 break;
1888 }
1889
1890 return AURA_STATE_NONE;
1891}
1892
1893SpellSpecificType SpellInfo::GetSpellSpecific() const
1894{
1895 switch (SpellFamilyName)
1896 {
1897 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
1898 {
1899 // Food / Drinks (mostly)
1900 if (AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_NOT_SEATED)
1901 {
1902 bool food = false;
1903 bool drink = false;
1904 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1905 {
1906 if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1907 continue;
1908 switch (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
1909 {
1910 // Food
1911 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_REGEN:
1912 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
1913 food = true;
1914 break;
1915 // Drink
1916 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN:
1917 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
1918 drink = true;
1919 break;
1920 default:
1921 break;
1922 }
1923 }
1924
1925 if (food && drink)
1926 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD_AND_DRINK;
1927 else if (food)
1928 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD;
1929 else if (drink)
1930 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_DRINK;
1931 }
1932 // scrolls effects
1933 else
1934 {
1935 SpellInfo const* firstRankSpellInfo = GetFirstRankSpell();
1936 switch (firstRankSpellInfo->Id)
1937 {
1938 case 8118: // Strength
1939 case 8099: // Stamina
1940 case 8112: // Spirit
1941 case 8096: // Intellect
1942 case 8115: // Agility
1943 case 8091: // Armor
1944 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SCROLL;
1945 case 12880: // Enrage (Enrage)
1946 case 57518: // Enrage (Wrecking Crew)
1947 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARRIOR_ENRAGE;
1948 }
1949 }
1950 break;
1951 }
1952 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
1953 {
1954 // family flags 18(Molten), 25(Frost/Ice), 28(Mage)
1955 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x12040000)
1956 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARMOR;
1957
1958 // Arcane brillance and Arcane intelect (normal check fails because of flags difference)
1959 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
1960 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARCANE_BRILLANCE;
1961
1962 if ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x1000000) && Effects[0].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE)
1963 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_POLYMORPH;
1964
1965 break;
1966 }
1967 case SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR:
1968 {
1969 if (Id == 12292) // Death Wish
1970 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARRIOR_ENRAGE;
1971
1972 break;
1973 }
1974 case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
1975 {
1976 // only warlock curses have this
1977 if (Dispel == DISPEL_CURSE)
1978 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_CURSE;
1979
1980 // Warlock (Demon Armor | Demon Skin | Fel Armor)
1981 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x20000020 || SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00000010)
1982 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARLOCK_ARMOR;
1983
1984 //seed of corruption and corruption
1985 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x10 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x2)
1986 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARLOCK_CORRUPTION;
1987 break;
1988 }
1989 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
1990 {
1991 // Divine Spirit and Prayer of Spirit
1992 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x20)
1993 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_PRIEST_DIVINE_SPIRIT;
1994
1995 break;
1996 }
1997 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
1998 {
1999 // only hunter stings have this
2000 if (Dispel == DISPEL_POISON)
2001 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_STING;
2002
2003 // only hunter aspects have this (but not all aspects in hunter family)
2004 if (SpellFamilyFlags.HasFlag(0x00380000, 0x00440000, 0x00001010))
2005 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_ASPECT;
2006
2007 break;
2008 }
2009 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
2010 {
2011 // Collection of all the seal family flags. No other paladin spell has any of those.
2012 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x26000C00
2013 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x0A000000)
2014 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL;
2015
2016 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00002190)
2017 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_HAND;
2018
2019 // Judgement of Wisdom, Judgement of Light, Judgement of Justice
2020 if (Id == 20184 || Id == 20185 || Id == 20186)
2021 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_JUDGEMENT;
2022
2023 // only paladin auras have this (for palaldin class family)
2024 if (SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00000020)
2025 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_AURA;
2026
2027 break;
2028 }
2029 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
2030 {
2031 // family flags 10 (Lightning), 42 (Earth), 37 (Water), proc shield from T2 8 pieces bonus
2032 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x420
2033 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000400
2034 || Id == 23552)
2035 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_ELEMENTAL_SHIELD;
2036
2037 break;
2038 }
2039 case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
2040 if (Id == 48266 || Id == 48263 || Id == 48265)
2041 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_PRESENCE;
2042 break;
2043 }
2044
2045 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2046 {
2047 if (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2048 {
2049 switch (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
2050 {
2051 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM:
2052 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET:
2053 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS:
2054 case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM:
2055 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_CHARM;
2056 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_CREATURES:
2057 /// @workaround For non-stacking tracking spells (We need generic solution)
2058 if (Id == 30645) // Gas Cloud Tracking
2059 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_NORMAL;
2060 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_RESOURCES:
2061 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_STEALTHED:
2062 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_TRACKER;
2063 }
2064 }
2065 }
2066
2067 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_NORMAL;
2068}

2157int32 SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost(Unit const* caster, SpellSchoolMask schoolMask) const
2158{
2159 // Spell drain all exist power on cast (Only paladin lay of Hands)
2160 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_DRAIN_ALL_POWER))
2161 {
2162 // If power type - health drain all
2163 if (PowerType == POWER_HEALTH)
2164 return caster->GetHealth();
2165 // Else drain all power
2166 if (PowerType < MAX_POWERS)
2167 return caster->GetPower(Powers(PowerType));
2168 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost: Unknown power type '%d' in spell %d", PowerType, Id);
2169 return 0;
2170 }
2171
2172 // Base powerCost
2173 int32 powerCost = ManaCost;
2174 // PCT cost from total amount
2175 if (ManaCostPercentage)
2176 {
2177 switch (PowerType)
2178 {
2179 // health as power used
2180 case POWER_HEALTH:
2181 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateHealth(), ManaCostPercentage));
2182 break;
2183 case POWER_MANA:
2184 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateMana(), ManaCostPercentage));
2185 break;
2186 case POWER_RAGE:
2187 case POWER_FOCUS:
2188 case POWER_ENERGY:
2189 case POWER_HAPPINESS:
2190 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxPower(Powers(PowerType)), ManaCostPercentage));
2191 break;
2192 case POWER_RUNE:
2193 case POWER_RUNIC_POWER:
2194 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "CalculateManaCost: Not implemented yet!");
2195 break;
2196 default:
2197 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "CalculateManaCost: Unknown power type '%d' in spell %d", PowerType, Id);
2198 return 0;
2199 }
2200 }
2201 SpellSchools school = GetFirstSchoolInMask(schoolMask);
2202 // Flat mod from caster auras by spell school
2203 powerCost += caster->GetInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_POWER_COST_MODIFIER + school);
2204
2205 // Shiv - costs 20 + weaponSpeed*10 energy (apply only to non-triggered spell with energy cost)
2206 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_SPELL_VS_EXTEND_COST))
2207 {
2208 uint32 speed = 0;
2209 if (SpellShapeshiftEntry const* ss = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(caster->GetShapeshiftForm()))
2210 speed = ss->attackSpeed;
2211 else
2212 {
2213 WeaponAttackType slot = BASE_ATTACK;
2214 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_REQ_OFFHAND))
2215 slot = OFF_ATTACK;
2216
2217 speed = caster->GetAttackTime(slot);
2218 }
2219
2220 powerCost += speed / 100;
2221 }
2222
2223 // Apply cost mod by spell
2224 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
2225 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(Id, SPELLMOD_COST, powerCost);
2226
2227 if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer())
2228 {
2229 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_LEVEL_DAMAGE_CALCULATION))
2230 {
2231 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(SpellLevel - 1);
2232 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(caster->getLevel() - 1);
2233 if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
2234 powerCost *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
2235 }
2236 }
2237
2238 // PCT mod from user auras by school
2239 powerCost = int32(powerCost * (1.0f + caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_FIELD_POWER_COST_MULTIPLIER + school)));
2240 if (powerCost < 0)
2241 powerCost = 0;
2242 return powerCost;
2243}

2282SpellInfo const* SpellInfo::GetAuraRankForLevel(uint8 level) const
2283{
2284 // ignore passive spells
2285 if (IsPassive())
2286 return this;
2287
2288 bool needRankSelection = false;
2289 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2290 {
2291 if (IsPositiveEffect(i) &&
2292 (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA ||
2293 Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PARTY ||
2294 Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID))
2295 {
2296 needRankSelection = true;
2297 break;
2298 }
2299 }
2300
2301 // not required
2302 if (!needRankSelection)
2303 return this;
2304
2305 for (SpellInfo const* nextSpellInfo = this; nextSpellInfo != NULL; nextSpellInfo = nextSpellInfo->GetPrevRankSpell())
2306 {
2307 // if found appropriate level
2308 if (uint32(level + 10) >= nextSpellInfo->SpellLevel)
2309 return nextSpellInfo;
2310
2311 // one rank less then
2312 }
2313
2314 // not found
2315 return NULL;
2316}

2323bool SpellInfo::IsDifferentRankOf(SpellInfo const* spellInfo) const
2324{
2325 if (Id == spellInfo->Id)
2326 return false;
2327 return IsRankOf(spellInfo);
2328}

2330bool SpellInfo::IsHighRankOf(SpellInfo const* spellInfo) const
2331{
2332 if (ChainEntry && spellInfo->ChainEntry)
2333 if (ChainEntry->first == spellInfo->ChainEntry->first)
2334 if (ChainEntry->rank > spellInfo->ChainEntry->rank)
2335 return true;
2336

2340void SpellInfo::_InitializeExplicitTargetMask()
2341{
2342 bool srcSet = false;
2343 bool dstSet = false;
2344 uint32 targetMask = Targets;
2345 // prepare target mask using effect target entries
2346 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2347 {
2348 if (!Effects[i].IsEffect())
2349 continue;
2350
2351 targetMask |= Effects[i].TargetA.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2352 targetMask |= Effects[i].TargetB.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2353
2354 // add explicit target flags based on spell effects which have EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT and no valid target provided
2355 if (Effects[i].GetImplicitTargetType() != EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT)
2356 continue;
2357
2358 // extend explicit target mask only if valid targets for effect could not be provided by target types
2359 uint32 effectTargetMask = Effects[i].GetMissingTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet, targetMask);
2360
2361 // don't add explicit object/dest flags when spell has no max range
2362 if (GetMaxRange(true) == 0.0f && GetMaxRange(false) == 0.0f)
2363 effectTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
2364
2365 targetMask |= effectTargetMask;
2366 }
2367
2368 ExplicitTargetMask = targetMask;
2369}

2371bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveEffect(uint8 effIndex, bool deep) const
2372{
2373 // not found a single positive spell with this attribute
2374 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NEGATIVE_1))
2375 return false;
2376
2377 switch (SpellFamilyName)
2378 {
2379 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
2380 switch (Id)
2381 {
2382 case 29214: // Wrath of the Plaguebringer
2383 case 34700: // Allergic Reaction
2384 case 54836: // Wrath of the Plaguebringer
2385 case 61987: // Avenging Wrath Marker
2386 case 61988: // Divine Shield exclude aura
2387 return false;
2388 case 30877: // Tag Murloc
2389 case 61716: // Rabbit Costume
2390 case 61734: // Noblegarden Bunny
2391 case 62344: // Fists of Stone
2392 case 61819: // Manabonked! (item)
2393 case 61834: // Manabonked! (minigob)
2394 return true;
2395 default:
2396 break;
2397 }
2398 break;
2399 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
2400 // Amplify Magic, Dampen Magic
2401 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] == 0x00002000)
2402 return true;
2403 // Ignite
2404 if (SpellIconID == 45)
2405 return true;
2406 break;
2407 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
2408 switch (Id)
2409 {
2410 case 64844: // Divine Hymn
2411 case 64904: // Hymn of Hope
2412 case 47585: // Dispersion
2413 return true;
2414 default:
2415 break;
2416 }
2417 break;
2418 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
2419 // Aspect of the Viper
2420 if (Id == 34074)
2421 return true;
2422 break;
2423 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
2424 if (Id == 30708)
2425 return false;
2426 break;
2427 case SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE:
2428 switch (Id)
2429 {
2430 // Envenom must be considered as a positive effect even though it deals damage
2431 case 32645: // Envenom (Rank 1)
2432 case 32684: // Envenom (Rank 2)
2433 case 57992: // Envenom (Rank 3)
2434 case 57993: // Envenom (Rank 4)
2435 return true;
2436 default:
2437 break;
2438 }
2439 break;
2440 default:
2441 break;
2442 }
2443
2444 switch (Mechanic)
2445 {
2446 case MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD:
2447 return true;
2448 default:
2449 break;
2450 }
2451
2452 // Special case: effects which determine positivity of whole spell
2453 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2454 {
2455 if (Effects[i].IsAura() && Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH)
2456 return true;
2457 }
2458
2459 switch (Effects[effIndex].Effect)
2460 {
2461 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
2462 // some explicitly required dummy effect sets
2463 switch (Id)
2464 {
2465 case 28441:
2466 return false; // AB Effect 000
2467 default:
2468 break;
2469 }
2470 break;
2471 // always positive effects (check before target checks that provided non-positive result in some case for positive effects)
2472 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
2473 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL:
2474 case SPELL_EFFECT_SKILL_STEP:
2475 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_PCT:
2476 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE_PCT:
2477 return true;
2478 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_ENEMY:
2479 return false;
2480
2481 // non-positive aura use
2482 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA:
2483 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_FRIEND:
2484 {
2485 switch (Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName)
2486 {
2487 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_DONE: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> negative)
2488 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STAT:
2489 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL:
2490 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DODGE_PERCENT:
2491 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT:
2492 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE:
2493 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE:
2494 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() < 0)
2495 return false;
2496 break;
2497 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_TAKEN: // dependent from bas point sign (positive -> negative)
2498 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2499 return false;
2500 break;
2501 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CRIT_PCT:
2502 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_CRIT_CHANCE:
2503 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2504 return true; // some expected positive spells have SPELL_ATTR1_NEGATIVE
2505 break;
2506 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER:
2507 return true;
2508 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
2509 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2510 if (!deep)
2511 {
2512 if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell))
2513 {
2514 // negative targets of main spell return early
2515 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2516 {
2517 if (!spellTriggeredProto->Effects[i].Effect)
2518 continue;
2519 // if non-positive trigger cast targeted to positive target this main cast is non-positive
2520 // this will place this spell auras as debuffs
2521 if (_IsPositiveTarget(spellTriggeredProto->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget(), spellTriggeredProto->Effects[i].TargetB.GetTarget()) && !spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
2522 return false;
2523 }
2524 }
2525 }
2526 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2527 // many positive auras have negative triggered spells at damage for example and this not make it negative (it can be canceled for example)
2528 break;
2529 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN: //have positive and negative spells, we can't sort its correctly at this moment.
2530 if (effIndex == 0 && Effects[1].Effect == 0 && Effects[2].Effect == 0)
2531 return false; // but all single stun aura spells is negative
2532 break;
2533 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE:
2534 if (Id == 24740) // Wisp Costume
2535 return true;
2536 return false;
2537 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT:
2538 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE:
2539 case SPELL_AURA_GHOST:
2540 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
2541 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STALKED:
2542 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
2543 case SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION:
2544 return false;
2545 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE: // used in positive spells also.
2546 // part of negative spell if cast at self (prevent cancel)
2547 if (Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
2548 return false;
2549 break;
2550 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED: // used in positive spells also
2551 // part of positive spell if cast at self
2552 if (Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
2553 return false;
2554 // but not this if this first effect (didn't find better check)
2555 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NEGATIVE_1) && effIndex == 0)
2556 return false;
2557 break;
2558 case SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY:
2559 {
2560 // non-positive immunities
2561 switch (Effects[effIndex].MiscValue)
2562 {
2563 case MECHANIC_BANDAGE:
2564 case MECHANIC_SHIELD:
2565 case MECHANIC_MOUNT:
2566 case MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY:
2567 return false;
2568 default:
2569 break;
2570 }
2571 break;
2572 }
2573 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER: // mods
2574 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER:
2575 {
2576 // non-positive mods
2577 switch (Effects[effIndex].MiscValue)
2578 {
2579 case SPELLMOD_COST: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> positive)
2580 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2581 {
2582 if (!deep)
2583 {
2584 bool negative = true;
2585 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2586 {
2587 if (i != effIndex)
2588 if (_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
2589 {
2590 negative = false;
2591 break;
2592 }
2593 }
2594 if (negative)
2595 return false;
2596 }
2597 }
2598 break;
2599 default:
2600 break;
2601 }
2602 break;
2603 }
2604 default:
2605 break;
2606 }
2607 break;
2608 }
2609 default:
2610 break;
2611 }
2612
2613 // non-positive targets
2614 if (!_IsPositiveTarget(Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget(), Effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetTarget()))
2615 return false;
2616
2617 // negative spell if triggered spell is negative
2618 if (!deep && !Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName && Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell)
2619 {
2620 if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell))
2621 if (!spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveSpell())
2622 return false;
2623 }
2624
2625 // ok, positive
2626 return true;
2627}

2629bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveSpell() const
2630{
2631 // spells with at least one negative effect are considered negative
2632 // some self-applied spells have negative effects but in self casting case negative check ignored.
2633 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2634 if (!_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
2635 return false;
2636 return true;
2637}

2639bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveTarget(uint32 targetA, uint32 targetB)
2640{
2641 // non-positive targets
2642 switch (targetA)
2643 {
2644 case TARGET_UNIT_NEARBY_ENEMY:
2645 case TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ENEMY:
2646 case TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ENEMY:
2647 case TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ENEMY:
2648 case TARGET_UNIT_CONE_ENEMY_24:
2649 case TARGET_UNIT_CONE_ENEMY_104:
2650 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY:
2651 case TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY:
2652 return false;
2653 default:
2654 break;
2655 }
2656 if (targetB)
2657 return _IsPositiveTarget(targetB, 0);
2658 return true;
2659}

2661void SpellInfo::_UnloadImplicitTargetConditionLists()
2662{
2663 // find the same instances of ConditionList and delete them.
2664 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2665 {
2666 ConditionContainer* cur = Effects[i].ImplicitTargetConditions;
2667 if (!cur)
2668 continue;
2669 for (uint8 j = i; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
2670 {
2671 if (Effects[j].ImplicitTargetConditions == cur)
2672 Effects[j].ImplicitTargetConditions = NULL;
2673 }
2674 delete cur;
2675 }
